We talked last week about market structure in thinly traded exotic over-the=
-counter products, where the market can be disrupted for months if a few tr=
aders switch jobs and have to be out on gardening leave.  I asked readers f=
or suggestions about how to game this dynamic for profit, and they  had goo=
d suggestions. Here=E2=80=99s another one, from a former=C2=A0exotics trade=
r, lightly edited to omit identifying details:Similar to inflation there ar=
e something like 5 traders who actually know what is going on in our market=
. In my experience the beauty of your trade is you don=E2=80=99t actually n=
eed to hire one of those 5 traders - you simply need one of them to have a =
big wedding or party in some far off location. When I was in the market eve=
ry trader knew each other, and one of those five relevant traders had a hug=
e, 4-day wedding=C2=A0attended by the entire market. The wedding sparked a =
week of chaos in the market as inexperienced market makers got run over by =
hedge funds.=C2=A0This seems like a cheaper trade to me: pay for one of the=
 market makers to throw a week long party on some remote island =E2=80=A6 h=
e will invite the entire market =E2=80=A6 run over whoever is left to quote=
 you prices while the entire market is off partying =E2=80=A6 wait for the =
real traders to sober up long enough to beg you to unwind at a handsome pro=
fit.=C2=A0
