om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Sanctions</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A common <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMDgvc29tZW9uZS1pcy1nb2luZy10by1kcmlsbC=
10aGUtb2lsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDMwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1057cda6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">problem</a>=C2=A0in environme=
ntal, social and governance investing is that if you own stock in a coal co=
mpany, and you care about ESG, so you sell that coal company stock, you are=
 sort of by definition selling it to someone who does=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</e=
m>care as much about ESG.[1] And then what?=C2=A0It is fairly straightforwa=
rd to say =E2=80=9CI care about ESG, so if someone comes to me looking to r=
aise money to open a coal mine, I won=E2=80=99t give it to her.=E2=80=9D Th=
at=E2=80=99s not what you=E2=80=99re doing. Selling publicly traded stock o=
n the secondary market is not quite the same as refusing to fund new activi=
ties. They are related. There is, you hope, some long-term effect: Your ref=
usal to buy coal companies on the secondary market will lower the expected =
returns on opening a coal mine, leading to less coal mining in the long run=
. But in the short run it means that people who like coal mines can buy the=
m cheap, and then the coal mines will all be owned by people who like coal =
mines.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here is a good <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
Ymxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDItMjgvaW52ZXN0b3JzLXNlbGxpbmc=
tcnVzc2lhbi1hc3NldHMtZmFjZS1mZXctb3B0aW9ucy1zdGVlcC1sb3NzZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMD=
MwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImd=
XRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMzAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB9cf3e257" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> Bloomberg News article</a> about how =E2=80=9CAnyone S=
elling Russian Assets Faces Few Options, Big Losses.=E2=80=9D One problem i=
s: Who is buying?</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For large sta=
kes, shareholders in Russian companies could try to find a buyer willing to=
 take over the holding wholesale. Sellers could try to appeal to investors =
in Asia, but this would carry its own political risk.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThere are potential long-term consequences of selling a=
ssets to the Chinese, especially if it means lesser Western exposure to or =
control or influence over commodities,=E2=80=9D said Mould.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">And the crippling international sanctions are making Russi=
an assets financially unattractive, even at steep discounts, meaning that C=
hinese investors may not want to risk the political headache either. =E2=80=
=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In an ironic twist, Russian investors c=
ould turn out to be the most obvious buyers for some assets.=C2=A0</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But there are huge obstacles that make transacting =
almost impossible in the short term. Stock trading on the local bourse was =
canceled, while the ruble plunged to an all-time low on Monday. This means =
buying global depositary receipts of Russian stocks being traded on exchang=
es such as London has also become prohibitively expensive for Moscow-based =
portfolio managers.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One =
quasi-solution is to just, like, forget about your Russian assets?</p><bloc=
kquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BP has warned that it could take a writ=
edown of as much as $25 billion from exiting Russia, as finding a buyer for=
 its 20% stake in Rosneft will be very challenging. Shell Plc is exiting it=
s Russian gas ventures, including a massive liquefied natural gas facility.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Other companies with significant investmen=
ts in Russia may opt to reduce the value of their holdings to zero. ...</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt is going to be difficult to find a=
 buyer with Russia gaining pariah status among the international community,=
=E2=80=9D Susannah Streeter, an analyst at Hargreaves Lansdown Plc, said of=
 BP=E2=80=99s planned retreat.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CFor=
 now, a very hefty writedown is likely to remain the main course of action,=
=E2=80=9D she said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=
=80=99t quite know what that means. You can say =E2=80=9Cwe paid $25 billio=
n for these assets, and now we can=E2=80=99t sell them, so we are going to =
forget all about them and mark them on our books at zero,=E2=80=9D but =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0you still own them, right? (If eventually things normalize and =
you are able to sell the stake and reverse the writedown, what did your big=
 public announcement that you=E2=80=99re divesting actually mean?)=C2=A0I s=
uppose you could donate them back to the company =E2=80=94=C2=A0call up Ros=
neft and say =E2=80=9Ccancel our shares, don=E2=80=99t bother paying us=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I am not sure that that=E2=80=99s a good way to i=
mpose sanctions=C2=A0<em>on Russia</em>; it is in some sense=C2=A0<em>good=
=C2=A0</em>for Rosneft (or Shell=E2=80=99s Russian partners in its joint ve=
ntures, etc.) to cancel equity claims on its business=C2=A0for free. If you=
=E2=80=99re writing the assets down to zero anyway I suppose one option (de=
pending on the mechanics of the sanctions regime) is to give them to charit=
y; there would be something a bit satisfying about a Ukraine relief charity=
 owning 20% of Rosneft.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is more =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZmYwZjA1MzMtY2E4Zi00ZTdiLTljZDgtMjg3MTBkY=
2VlNWY3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2ca5bc2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">from the Financial Times=
</a>=C2=A0about the difficulties of trying to sell Russian assets back to R=
ussian investors:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One question =
for brokers and investors was whether their trading counterparts would be e=
jected from Swift. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m having to not trade Russia till I g=
et a list,=E2=80=9D said one trader at an investment bank.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Some brokers were concerned that even if they managed to st=
rike a deal, there was little guarantee it would be settled and the asset e=
xchanged for cash. Most cross-border trades are settled in US dollars, and =
banks are responsible for managing the currency risk for such transactions.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s just so messy. If yo=
u trade something and you can=E2=80=99t settle it, you=E2=80=99re left with=
 the exposure,=E2=80=9D said a trader at a US broker.</p></blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, this is one of those things where in the sho=
rt run =E2=80=9CRussian buyers can buy stock and not pay for it=E2=80=9D wo=
uld seem in some sense beneficial to Russia, though in the long run <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDMtMDEvcnVzc2lhbi1tYXJr=
ZXRzLXN0YXJ0LXRvLWxvb2stdW5pbnZlc3RhYmxlLWFzLXNhbmN0aW9ucy1iaXRlP2NtcGlkPUJ=
CRDAzMDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dG=
VyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDMwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB1cbe43fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> it is bad for Russia</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe calamity of Russia=E2=80=99s war in Ukrai=
ne has put an end to international financial investing in Russia,=E2=80=9D =
said Christopher Granville, managing director for EMEA and global political=
 research at TS Lombard in London.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Elsewhere if you own Russian bonds it seems increasingly plausib=
le that you might not get paid interest, because it might be illegal in Rus=
sia for the issuer to pay interest, and illegal in the West for intermediar=
ies to pass along that interest. From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZmY=
wZjA1MzMtY2E4Zi00ZTdiLTljZDgtMjg3MTBkY2VlNWY3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCc2ca=
5bc2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">the FT</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those=
 concerns were exacerbated by worries that payments for trades and coupons =
on bonds would be frozen in accounts at custodian banks or international se=
curities depositories, where deals are settled and balances between central=
 banks and commercial banks are updated.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
e two largest depositories, Belgium=E2=80=99s Euroclear and Clearstream, to=
gether hold about =E2=82=AC50tn of assets in custody for global investors, =
making them a pillar of the financial system. Deals are usually finalised b=
y transferring balances between customer accounts held at the depository, o=
r between the two market utilities.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Late on=
 Monday, Clearstream said the rouble would no longer be an eligible settlem=
ent currency, with immediate effect. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">BlackRock believes it is possible that Russia could default on its bond=
s because of an inability to make payments to investors=E2=80=99 accounts. =
=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s the difference between ability to pay and desire to p=
ay,=E2=80=9D said Rieder.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And =
Bloomberg reports that it looked briefly like it might be illegal for Russi=
an companies to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26=
873872.266605/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItM=
DItMjgvcHV0aW4tYmFucy1ydXNzaWFucy1mcm9tLXNlcnZpY2luZy1mb3JlaWduLWRlYnQtb3Zl=
ci1zYW5jdGlvbnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ=
1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMzAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leX=
N0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe44f5190" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> service their debts</a>=
:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">President Vladimir Putin bann=
ed all Russian residents from transferring foreign currency abroad, hardeni=
ng capital controls as part of a package of retaliatory measures for U.S. a=
nd European sanctions over his invasion of Ukraine.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">The steps, which take effect March 1, include a ban on payments of=
 hard currency made to foreigners =E2=80=9Cin connection with loan agreemen=
ts,=E2=80=9D according to the text of the decree published Monday.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The central bank later issued a clarification, sayi=
ng the ban =E2=80=9Conly covers new loans and not servicing of existing deb=
t.=E2=80=9D Some investors and economists had said the phrasing could amoun=
t to a default.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile buyi=
ng <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26873872.266605=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDMtMDEvZ2xvYm=
